1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,050
Build your own sell-yourself, to-yourself commercial.

2
00:00:04,240 --> 00:00:09,250
Think for a moment about one of America's most popular products, Coca-Cola.

3
00:00:09,601 --> 00:00:16,131
Every day, your eyes or ears come in contact many times with the good news about Coke.

4
00:00:16,961 --> 00:00:23,091
The people who make Coca-Cola are continually reselling you on Coke, and for a good reason.

5
00:00:23,201 --> 00:00:29,490
If they stopped reselling you, chances are you'd grow lukewarm and eventually cold to Coke.

6
00:00:29,601 --> 00:00:31,571
Then sales would drop.

7
00:00:32,081 --> 00:00:35,731
But the Coca-Cola company isn't going to let this happen.

8
00:00:35,921 --> 00:00:40,611
They resell you and resell you and resell you on Coke.

9
00:00:41,121 --> 00:00:46,770
Every day, you and I see half-alive people who are no longer sold on themselves.

10
00:00:47,201 --> 00:00:51,731
They lack self-respect for their most important product, themselves.

11
00:00:51,921 --> 00:00:53,651
These folks are indifferent.

12
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:55,010
They feel small.

13
00:00:55,201 --> 00:00:56,770
They feel like nobodies.

14
00:00:56,770 --> 00:00:59,971
And because they feel that way, that's what they are.

15
00:01:01,041 --> 00:01:05,171
The half-alive person needs to be resold on himself.

16
00:01:05,281 --> 00:01:08,691
He needs to realize that he's a first-class person.

17
00:01:08,881 --> 00:01:12,290
He needs honest, sincere belief in himself.

18
00:01:12,881 --> 00:01:17,490
Tom Staley is a young fellow who is going places, and fast.

19
00:01:17,841 --> 00:01:27,331
Tom regularly resells himself on himself three times every day, with what he calls Tom Staley's 60-second commercial.

20
00:01:27,681 --> 00:01:32,371
He carries his personalized commercial in his billfold at all times.

21
00:01:32,561 --> 00:01:34,691
Here is exactly what it says.

22
00:01:35,281 --> 00:01:41,010
Tom Staley, meet Tom Staley, an important, a really important person.

23
00:01:41,201 --> 00:01:44,530
Tom, you're a big thinker, so think big.

24
00:01:44,881 --> 00:01:47,010
Think big about everything.

25
00:01:47,201 --> 00:01:52,611
You've got plenty of ability to do a first-class job, so do a first-class job.

26
00:01:52,961 --> 00:01:57,250
Tom, you believe in happiness, progress, and prosperity.

27
00:01:57,361 --> 00:02:00,131
So, talk only happiness.

28
00:02:00,321 --> 00:02:02,050
Talk only progress.

29
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:04,131
Talk only prosperity.

30
00:02:04,481 --> 00:02:06,290
You have lots of drive, Tom.

31
00:02:06,481 --> 00:02:07,651
Lots of drive.

32
00:02:07,841 --> 00:02:09,810
So put that drive to work.

33
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,810
Nothing can stop you, Tom.

34
00:02:11,921 --> 00:02:12,691
Nothing.

35
00:02:13,041 --> 00:02:15,331
Tom, you're enthusiastic.

36
00:02:15,521 --> 00:02:17,971
Let your enthusiasm show through.

37
00:02:18,161 --> 00:02:20,851
You look good, Tom, and you feel good.

38
00:02:20,961 --> 00:02:22,131
Stay that way.

39
00:02:22,721 --> 00:02:29,091
Tom Staley, you were a great fellow yesterday, and you're going to be an even greater fellow today.

40
00:02:29,281 --> 00:02:31,171
Now, go to it, Tom.

41
00:02:31,361 --> 00:02:32,691
Go forward.

42
00:02:34,801 --> 00:02:40,451
Tom credits his commercial with helping him become a more successful, dynamic person.

43
00:02:41,121 --> 00:02:49,331
Before I started selling myself to myself, says Tom, I thought I was inferior to just about anybody and everybody.

44
00:02:49,601 --> 00:02:54,050
Now, I realize that I've got what it takes to win, and I'm winning,

45
00:02:54,161 --> 00:02:56,211
and I'm always going to win.

46
00:02:56,801 --> 00:03:01,250
Here's how to build your sell-yourself-to-yourself commercial.

47
00:03:01,521 --> 00:03:05,571
First, select your assets, your points of superiority.

48
00:03:05,841 --> 00:03:08,691
Ask yourself, what are my best qualities?

49
00:03:08,881 --> 00:03:11,411
Don't be shy in describing yourself.

50
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:16,131
Next, put these points down on paper in your own words.

51
00:03:16,401 --> 00:03:18,371
Write your commercial to you.

52
00:03:18,561 --> 00:03:20,931
Reread Tom Staley's commercial.

53
00:03:21,121 --> 00:03:23,250
Notice how he talks to Tom.

54
00:03:23,361 --> 00:03:24,611
Talk to yourself.

55
00:03:24,721 --> 00:03:26,050
Be very direct.

56
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:30,211
Don't think of anyone but you as you say your commercial.

57
00:03:31,041 --> 00:03:36,290
Third, practice your commercial out loud in private at least once a day.

58
00:03:36,561 --> 00:03:39,171
It helps a lot to do this before a mirror.

59
00:03:39,281 --> 00:03:41,010
Put your body into it.

60
00:03:41,281 --> 00:03:44,611
Repeat your commercial forcefully with determination.

61
00:03:44,881 --> 00:03:47,891
Make your blood travel faster through your body.

62
00:03:47,921 --> 00:03:49,731
Get yourself warmed up.

63
00:03:50,481 --> 00:03:55,010
Fourth, read your commercial silently several times every day.

64
00:03:55,281 --> 00:03:58,851
Read it before you tackle anything that demands courage.

65
00:03:58,961 --> 00:04:01,411
Read it every time you feel let down.

66
00:04:01,441 --> 00:04:05,250
Keep your commercial handy at all times, then use it.

67
00:04:06,401 --> 00:04:07,971
Just one thing more.